  "prompt": "What is the best thing to do for your wife if your father-in-law dies from a prolonged illness?",
  "response": "When your wife is grieving the loss of her father, the best things you can do include:\n\n1. Emotional support\n- Be present and listen\n- Allow her to express her emotions\n- Validate her feelings\n- Offer comfort and hugs\n\n2. Practical help\n- Assist with funeral arrangements\n- Help with paperwork and administrative tasks\n- Take care of daily chores and responsibilities\n- Coordinate with family members\n\n3. Provide space when needed\n- Understand she may need alone time\n- Respect her grieving process\n- Be patient and understanding\n\n4. Offer specific support\n- Help her process memories of her father\n- Support her through potential grief counseling\n- Attend memorial services together\n- Help her maintain connections with her family\n\n5. Long-term care\n- Continue to check in on her emotional state\n- Be aware grief can come in waves\n- Offer ongoing compassion and understanding\n- Help her remember and honor her father's memory\n\n6. Personal self-care\n- Take care of your own emotional needs\n- Seek support if needed\n- Maintain open communication with your wife\n\nThe most important things are to be genuinely supportive, loving, and present during this difficult time.",
